<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5032994>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 14. Plesiastropecten hallovensis Peyer, 1944. A. Holotype (MZA L13a), the original of Peyer (1944: pl. 7) and Blake (1984: fig. 1a–h). B. Enlargement of distal arm. C–F. Line drawings of MZA L 13b/32a–e. C. Ossicle distribution of entire individual; note large, stellate abactinal ossicles which each carry a large boss for attachment of a single spine. D. Ambulacral ossicle, in abactinal view, and two abactinal ossicles. E. Adambulacral ossicle with spines attached. F. Two marginal ossicles, with serrated spines attached. Provenance: Lower Jurassic (Hettangian, liasicus ammonite Zone) of Hallau, Canton Schaffhausen, Switzerland. Scale bars: A = 10 mm; B–C = 5 mm; D–G = 2 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5032994/files/figure.png" .
